Japan Backs Philippine School-Building Program
MANILA , November 15 ( Xinhua ) -- Japan was committed to helping the Philippines build 630 elementary and secondary school buildings nationwide over a six-year period , a government news release said Sunday .
In a recent meeting with Philippine officials , representatives of the Japan International Cooperation Agency said the agency would build 89 school buildings in three Philippine regions in support of an education project aiming to increase the number of classrooms to 21,514 in 1999 from this year 's 14 , 615 .
As the implementing arm of Japan 's foreign-assisted projects , the agency will build the elementary and secondary school buildings starting in March next year .
These school buildings will be composed of classrooms and science laboratories with basic educational equipment , Philippine officials said .
